The paper discusses predictive performance modeling for distributed batch processing, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of machine learning techniques for predicting performance metrics also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the challenges of scheduling and resource allocation, which are topics related to software engineering (cs.SE) and performance analysis (cs.PF). Finally, the use of past performance observations to predict future performance suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
